						<div class="postbody">In Nintendulator and my emulator, if you reset Micro Machines, it crashes the CPU (it jumps to a bad location and executes a KIL instruction).  But, I have yet to figure out why.  It must be sensitive to initial memory values or the state of the CPU.  Anyone have a clue on this one?</div>

