						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I want you to try a soft reset in your emulator, but try it twice in a row. If the first leads to a STP (also called KIL), the second may cause execution to continue.<br /><br />Or am I misunderstanding what you meant by &quot;a crashed CPU&quot;? Is your emulator's core actually crashing? Or does a soft reset fail to pull it out of STP?</div><br /><br />Ah.  I understand now.  <br /><br />The second reset does pull it out of the halt state; however, it shortly thereafter executes the same KIL instruction that halted it on the first reset.  Successive resets produce more halts.<br /><br />Edit: For testing purposes, I modified my emulator to clear main memory and vram on reset, to reset all the mapper banks and to clear all the CPU registers and flags.  And, the CPU still jams on reset!  That's really strange.  Some other state information is causing this.</div>

