A Y:01 P:A5 SP:FA CYC: 51 SL:241 <br />9EC7&nbsp; 33 99&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;RLA ($99),Y = 0000 @ 0001 = 78&nbsp; A:01 X:FA Y:01 P:24 SP:FA CYC: 66 SL:241 <br />9EC9&nbsp; CC E6 72&nbsp; CPY $72E6 = 00&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A:01 X:FA Y:01 P:25 SP:FA CYC: 90 SL:241 <br />9ECC&nbsp; 90 3C&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;BCC $9F0A&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A:01 X:FA Y:01 P:25 SP:FA CYC:102 SL:241 <br />9ECE&nbsp; 18&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; CLC&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A:01 X:FA Y:01 P:24 SP:FA CYC:108 SL:241 <br />9ECF&nbsp; 00&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; BRK&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A:01 X:FA Y:01 P:24 SP:F7 CYC:114 SL:241 <br />FFFF&nbsp; FF 00 F1&nbsp; ISB $F100,X @ F1FA = 53&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A:AC X:FA Y:01 P:A4 SP:F7 CYC:135 SL:241</div><br /><br />The deviation happens at that spontaneous jump to $0300.  From the SL, it coincides with NMI.  Prior to the jump, it was in loop that was decrementing X to 0.  I will keep investigating.<br /><br />Edit:<br /><br />The last bank in mapper 71 is fixed.  Here is the NMI address:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp;0F:FFFA:00&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; BRK <br />&nbsp;0F:FFFB:03&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; UNDEFINED</div><br /><br />NMI directs execution to code loaded into RAM.<br /><br />Edit 2:<br /><br />I can fix the problem by writing $00 to the PPU CTRL register ($2000) on reset, disabling NMI's.  Should that be happening?</div>

